---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  path="/brass-lessons"
  title="Brass Lessons in McKinney, TX | Trumpet, French Horn, Tuba | Anthem Music"
  description="Private brass lessons in downtown McKinney — trumpet, french horn, and tuba. Build tone, breath support, range, and technique one-on-one. Band and orchestra referrals available. Book a consultation.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center;">Trumpet · French Horn · Tuba</span>
      <h1 class="center">Brass lessons in McKinney</h1>
      <p class="lead mx-auto center">Private, one-on-one instruction on anything with three valves — building the tone, breath, and technique that make brass playing feel effortless.</p>
      <div class="center" style="margin-top:1.8rem;"><a href="/schedule" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Consultation</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>Tone comes first</h2>
      <p>Brass is different from other instruments: before fingerings or reading, there's the sound itself. Breath support, embouchure, and buzzing fundamentals determine everything a brass player will ever do — tone, range, endurance, and control all grow from the same root. We build that foundation carefully, because a student with a good sound and solid air will progress faster on everything else.</p>
      <p>From there, lessons cover reading, valve technique, articulation, and range development — alongside the same musical framework every Anthem student gets: scales, patterns, and the why behind the music they're playing. Whether a student plays for themselves or is building toward ensemble work, the fundamentals are the same.</p>

      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature"><h3>Breath &amp; Tone</h3><p>Air support and embouchure fundamentals that make everything else possible.</p></div>
        <div class="feature"><h3>Technique &amp; Range</h3><p>Valve work, articulation, and steady, healthy range development.</p></div>
        <div class="feature"><h3>One-on-One</h3><p>Private lessons tailored to the student — a different world from a 40-kid band hall.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2>Playing in a band or orchestra?</h2>
      <p>Private lessons are the fastest way for a band student to stand out — section leaders and chair placements are usually the kids getting individual instruction. And if your student wants the full ensemble experience, we'll help there too: we partner with <a href="https://texashomeschoolmusic.org/J/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Texas Homeschool Music</a> and a network of local programs for concert band, marching band, and orchestra placement. If we're not the right fit for something, we'll point you to who is.</p>

      <h2>What a first lesson looks like</h2>
      <p>Every new student starts with a consultation — experience, goals, instrument condition, and a first look at fundamentals. Renting or buying an instrument? Ask us first; we'll save you money and headaches.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <div><h2>Start playing brass</h2><p>Book a consultation and we'll build a plan around your student's goals — school band, personal enjoyment, or both.</p></div>
      <a href="/schedule" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-hero { background: var(--cream-soft); padding: clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem) 0; }
  .page-hero h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .narrow { max-width: 760px; }
  .narrow h2 { margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .narrow h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .narrow p { color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .narrow a { color: var(--orange); font-weight: 600; }
  .feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2.5rem 0; }
  .feature { background: var(--cream-soft); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.6rem; }
  .feature h3 { color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.15rem; }
  .feature p { color: var(--gray); font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0; }
  .cta-band { background: var(--orange); padding: clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem) 0; }
  .cta-inner { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 2rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .cta-band h2 { color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .cta-band p { color: var(--white); opacity: 0.92; max-width: 46ch; }
  .cta-band .btn-primary { background: var(--white); color: var(--orange-dark); }
  .cta-band .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--navy); color: var(--cream); }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { .feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
